Smartphone maker OPPO on Thursday launched the new OPPO A Series 2020 in Nairobi. The new OPPO A Series 2020, which includes the OPPO A9 2020 and OPPO A5 2020 models, is the brand’s latest offer for the mid-level smartphone market. “We named the OPPO A Series 2020 in celebration of the beginning of the new decade, also to commemorate the success of A series over the past ten years while welcoming a whole new generation of mobile users,” said Muthoni Wachira, OPPO Kenya. She added; “This new name also reflects our vision for the coming ten years. It highlights the brand’s latest technologies, stunning design, superb photography, powerful performance and perfect tuning to the needs of young people. Now, with the latest upgrade, the OPPO A Series 2020 will offer more possibilities than ever before!” The OPPO A Series 2020 has a multifunctional 48MP Quad Camera that pushes the boundary of creativity, and a 5,000mAh Ultra Battery that provides longer use. Its impressively versatile camera technology broadens users’ creative horizons, and the whole handset offers an immersive entertainment experience and powerful performance. The OPPO A5/A9 2020 both comes with a multipurpose Quad Camera setup, including a 48MP Main Camera + 8MP Ultra-Wide Lens + 2MP Mono Lens + 2MP Portrait Lens. The OPPO A5 2020 also comes with a multipurpose Quad Camera setup but with a 12MP Main Camera. The A9 2020 is equipped with 16MP selfie camera while A5 2020 with 8MP selfie camera, both using AI Beautification technology for tailor-made selfies to better cater to different markets and beauty trends. This technology automatically identifies skin tone, age, gender, and skin colour. The OPPO A Series 2020 also comes equipped with a new and more compact waterdrop screen, with a 31.4 per cent decrease in the overall area compared to the previous generation, for a better look and user experience. Large capacity 5000mAh battery enables all-day use, capable of supporting 19 hours of continuous operation. The battery is also able to handle reverse charging, freeing active, and on-the-go users from the worries of rapid battery drain. On top of that, the OPPO A Series 2020 packs an ultra-powerful performance, thanks to the Qualcomm Snapdragon 665 platform, with an 8-core 64-bit processor. The A series 2020 is powered by ColorOS 6, based on Android 9.0, providing a fresh visual experience that’s more sleek, refined and comfortable even after prolonged use.